title: Eurozone finance ministers likely to resume talks on Greek bailout
text:
Eurozone finance ministers are expected to resume talks on a Greek bailout deal in Brussels.
According to BBC, Dutch Finance Minister Jeroen Dijsselbloem said, nine hours after talks ended without agreement on Saturday, that the negotiations are “very difficult”.
The finance ministers believe that Athens is unlikely to implement austerity measures it has proposed.
They have little time to produce a working plan ready for European leaders, who meet in Brussels later on Sunday.
First Published on July 12, 2015 12:11 pm
